        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): preserve audio and video input modalities",
        "body": "Closes #97048\n\nAI-assisted.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where generated provider model catalogs containing `audio` or `video` input modalities were rejected or later narrowed back to `text`/`image`, causing valid fetched models such as MiniMax-M3 or multimodal Phi rows to be dropped or misreported.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe model catalog and resolved-model input contract now accepts and preserves `audio` and `video` alongside existing text/image/document catalog metadata. The change updates the schema, catalog normalization, runtime/static provider conversion, OpenAI Codex image-compat augmentation, configured list rows, and model-list row rendering so the widened contract is not lost in later paths.\n\n## User Impact\n\nAgents can keep valid provider-fetched multimodal model entries instead of falling back because a catalog row included audio or video input support. `openclaw models list` also reports those accepted modalities instead of silently dropping them.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/openai/openai-chatgpt-provider.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.inline-provider.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.static-catalog.test.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/model-catalog-core/src/model-catalog-normalize.test.ts src/agents/sessions/model-registry.test.ts src/model-catalog/provider-index/normalize.test.ts src/commands/models/list.model-row.test.ts src/commands/models/list.rows.test.ts src/commands/models/list.list-command.forward-compat.test.ts src/commands/models.list.e2e.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD && git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n",
